The 20 horses that will compete in the special event have already been chosen, and the final wagers have been placed on which stallions will compete. This year's Durban July Final field looks to be one for the record books.

Leading as the race favorite is See It Again, weighing 56.5, and ridden by Pierre Strydom. With 33/10 odds, See It Again won the most recent Daily News 2000 race and has been trained by Michael Roberts to win again.

However, it will have to outdo some strong competition, including two-time Hollywood Durban July winner Do It Again, who has had 34 runs (including 5 Hollywoodbets Durban July races) and 9 wins and also intends to make 2023 a winning year. Below is a table of the horses, trainers, and jockeys competing in this widely anticipated event:

